## Directory layout

```
{{kb_path}}/
├── CLAUDE.md                    # This file
├── raw/
│   ├── bookmarks.jsonl          # Canonical bookmark store (sync.py writes; do not hand-edit)
│   └── bookmarks/               # Topic batches (preprocess.py writes; do not hand-edit)
│       ├── _manifest.md
│       └── <topic>.md
├── wiki/                        # Claude-only synthesized pages
│   ├── index.md                 # Master catalog (markdown table)
│   ├── log.md                   # Chronological audit log
│   ├── queries/                 # Saved query-result pages
│   └── <topic-pages>.md
├── notes/                       # User-only personal notes — Claude never reads or writes here
├── .twitter-wiki/
│   ├── sync-meta.json           # Sync state (cursor, last sync time, count)
│   ├── cluster-map.json         # Topic → match rules (Claude generates)
│   └── ingest-state.json        # Which batches were synthesized at which sizes
├── .obsidian/                   # Obsidian vault config
└── .gitignore
```

**Hard rule:** `wiki/` is Claude's. `notes/` is the user's. They never overlap. Claude never reads `notes/`. The user never edits files in `wiki/` (they may *delete* a wiki page they don't want, but they don't edit content — that gets clobbered on the next ingest).

