## Source classification & extraction

For **tweets/threads** (the only source type for v1):

- Extract the **core insight** plus enough surrounding context to make it standalone.
- Include **author handle** and a link to the original tweet.
- For tweets with >1000 likes, **include a short direct quote** in addition to the synthesis.
- Note when the author's bio/expertise is relevant to evaluating the claim ("Andrej Karpathy is a former director of AI at Tesla, so..." — but be brief).
- Engagement metrics (likes/retweets) are useful but not authoritative — virality ≠ correctness. Note when something is high-engagement but methodologically weak.
- Skip tweets that are pure media (no text), pure links with no commentary, or low-value engagement bait.

If a future version adds articles or longer-form sources, extraction depth will scale up.

